	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The `hasBoundaryConnectionPoint` relation means the `ConnectionPoint` represents the boundary of a `System` (see {s223:System}) defined by the modeler, such as a model fragment provided by the vendor of a collection of equipment intended for integration with another model. The presence of this relation is used to indicate that such a \"dangling connection point\" should not generate a validation error in a non-integrated context but should generate an error in an integrated context." ;
