<http://data.ashrae.org/standard223#QuantifiableActuatableProperty> a <http://data.ashrae.org/standard223#Class> , <http://www.w3.org/ns/shacl#NodeShape> ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "This class is for instances of `QuantifiableProperty` for which numerical values are specified to be modifiable by a user or a machine outside of the model, like a setpoint." ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Quantifiable actuatable property" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://data.ashrae.org/standard223#QuantifiableProperty> , <http://data.ashrae.org/standard223#ActuatableProperty> .
<http://data.ashrae.org/standard223#ActuatableProperty> a <http://data.ashrae.org/standard223#Class> , <http://www.w3.org/ns/shacl#NodeShape> ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The term \"actuatable\" implies that writing to the `ActuatableProperty` value will directly trigger a physical actuation by either an `Actuator` or `Equipment`.\nIn contrast, the term \"observable\" (see {s223:ObservableProperty}) implies that reading the `ObservableProperty` value will return the result of a physical observation." ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Actuatable property" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://data.ashrae.org/standard223#Property> .
<http://data.ashrae.org/standard223#AC-277VLN-1Ph-60Hz> a <http://data.ashrae.org/standard223#Class> , <http://data.ashrae.org/standard223#AC-277VLN-1Ph-60Hz> , <http://www.w3.org/ns/shacl#NodeShape> ;
	<http://data.ashrae.org/standard223#hasACLineNeutralVoltage> <http://data.ashrae.org/standard223#Voltage-277V> ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "`AC-277VLN-1Ph-60Hz`" ;
	<http://data.ashrae.org/standard223#hasFrequency> <http://data.ashrae.org/standard223#Frequency-60Hz> ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "AC-277VLN-1Ph-60Hz" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://data.ashrae.org/standard223#Electricity-AC> ;
	<http://data.ashrae.org/standard223#hasNumberOfElectricalPhases> <http://data.ashrae.org/standard223#NumberOfElectricalPhases-SinglePhase> .
<http://data.ashrae.org/standard223#Medium-Mix> a <http://data.ashrae.org/standard223#Class> , <http://data.ashrae.org/standard223#Medium-Mix> , <http://www.w3.org/ns/shacl#NodeShape> ;
	<http://www.w3.org/ns/shacl#property> _:d5eacee3c82eb9c35573acd62c327d85 ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "\nThis class and its subclasses represent substances that are composed of constituents. The components of a `Medium-Mix` can be modeled using the relations `composedOf` and `ofConstituent`. See Figure 10-8a and Figure 10-8b.\n\nFigure 10-8a shows `GlycolSolution-30Percent`, itself a subclass of\n`Water-GlycolSolution`, `Fluid-Water`, and `Mix-Fluid`, with a _Water Concentration_\nproperty referencing 70% `Constituent-H2O` by the relation `ofConstituent` and\na _Glycol Concentration_ property referencing 30% `Constituent-Glycol` also\nby the relation `ofConstituent`.\n\nFigure 10-8b shows `PowerAndSignal-PoE`, itself a subclass of `Mix-PowerAndSignal`,\ncomposed of a _Power_ `Property` referencing `Electricity-DC` and a _Communications_\n`Property` referencing `Signal-WiredEthernet`.\n\n![ ](figures/Figure_10-8_Substance.svg)\n\n: Medium-Mix Enumerations\n\n| Enumeration |\n|:-----------|\n| `Mix-Fluid` (see {s223:Mix-Fluid}) |\n| `Mix-PowerAndSignal` (see {s223:Mix-PowerAndSignal}) |" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Mixed medium" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://data.ashrae.org/standard223#Substance-Medium> .
<http://data.ashrae.org/standard223#Aspect-Manufacturer> a <http://data.ashrae.org/standard223#Class> , <http://data.ashrae.org/standard223#Aspect-Manufacturer> , <http://www.w3.org/ns/shacl#NodeShape> ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The property value is a name or other identifier of the product’s manufacturer." ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Manufacturer" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://data.ashrae.org/standard223#EnumerationKind-Aspect> .
<http://data.ashrae.org/standard223#Domain-Electrical> a <http://data.ashrae.org/standard223#Class> , <http://data.ashrae.org/standard223#Domain-Electrical> , <http://www.w3.org/ns/shacl#NodeShape> ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The domain that represents equipment that distributes and monitors electrical power within a building. Example `Domain-Electrical` equipment include `ElectricityBreaker`, `ElectricEnergyConverter`, and `ElectricityMeter`." ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Electrical domain" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://data.ashrae.org/standard223#EnumerationKind-Domain> .
