<http://data.ashrae.org/standard223#hasPhysicalLocation> a <http://data.ashrae.org/standard223#Relation> , <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#Property> ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A `Relation` that associates a piece of `Equipment` with its physical location (i.e., in a `PhysicalSpace`). The physical location of a piece of `Equipment` is not necessarily the same as the location affected by the operation of the `Equipment`. For example, an air handler may physically be located on the roof, but its effect is to provide conditioned air to a `Zone` or `DomainSpace` within the building. By following the path of connections, it can be determined what other equipment or spaces are possibly impacted by the `Equipment`." ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "has physical location" .
<http://data.ashrae.org/standard223/1.0/extensions/g36#ChilledWaterValveAnnotation> <http://www.w3.org/ns/shacl#targetClass> <http://data.ashrae.org/standard223#Valve> ;
